<DocLayout title="CLI Installation" description="Installing and configuring the Yet.Project CLI tool.">
  <h1>CLI Installation</h1>

  <p>
    The Yet.Project CLI lets you manage tasks and projects from your terminal without leaving your editor.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>

  <h3>npm (Recommended)</h3>
  <pre><code>npm install -g @yet/cli</code></pre>

  <h3>yarn</h3>
  <pre><code>yarn global add @yet/cli</code></pre>

  <h3>pnpm</h3>
  <pre><code>pnpm add -g @yet/cli</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify Installation</h2>

  <pre><code>{`yet --version
# yet-cli v1.0.0`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>

  <p>Login with your API key:</p>

  <pre><code>{`yet login --key yet_your_api_key_here

# Or interactively
yet login
# Paste your API key when prompted`}</code></pre>

  <p>The CLI stores your credentials in <code>~/.yet/config.json</code>.</p>

  <h2>Quick Test</h2>

  <pre><code>{`# List your projects
yet project list

# Should show your projects:
# MYAPP  My Application  12 tasks
# DOCS   Documentation   5 tasks`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>

  <h3>Default Project</h3>
  <p>Set a default project to avoid typing <code>--project</code> every time:</p>

  <pre><code>{`yet config set defaultProject MYAPP

# Now you can run:
yet task list
# Instead of:
yet task list --project MYAPP`}</code></pre>

  <h3>Output Format</h3>
  <p>Choose your preferred output format:</p>

  <pre><code>{`# Table format (default)
yet config set format table

# JSON format (for scripting)
yet config set format json

# Minimal format
yet config set format minimal`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Shell Completion</h2>

  <h3>Bash</h3>
  <pre><code>{`yet completion bash >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc`}</code></pre>

  <h3>Zsh</h3>
  <pre><code>{`yet completion zsh >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc`}</code></pre>

  <h3>Fish</h3>
  <pre><code>{`yet completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/yet.fish`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Uninstalling</h2>

  <pre><code>{`npm uninstall -g @yet/cli

# Remove config
rm -rf ~/.yet`}</code></pre>

